radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild prominence of the extrahepatic biliary tree (maximum diameter of 13 mm), no upstream dilatation of intrahepatic bile ducts, smooth contour of bile ducts without stenosis or thickening, anomalous low insertion of the right posterior bile duct, normal liver size and contour, normal parenchymal signal of the liver, no focal hepatic lesion, unremarkable pancreas, pancreatic duct, spleen, right kidney and adrenal glands, 1.5 cm hemorrhagic cyst in the left mid kidney, no lymphadenopathy or ascites, mild atelectatic changes noted at each lung base.
